modules.description: This module implements low-level bit manipulation and hashing operations used in the splittable PRNG algorithm. It provides functions for mixing and transforming 64-bit integer values, specifically tailored for generating high-quality random numbers with guaranteed uniqueness properties. These operations are used internally to implement the core random number generation and splitting logic.

This module implements a purely functional splittable pseudorandom number generator (PRNG) that supports deterministic splitting into independent sub-generators. It operates on a state type `t` and provides functions to generate random integers (64-bit, signed, non-negative, bounded), booleans, and split or vary the generator state. Concrete use cases include generating unique random values in parallel computations, randomized algorithms requiring independent streams, and testing scenarios needing reproducible randomness.
